title: 14-year-old Sullivan County boy dies in shooting
content:
SULLIVAN COUNTY, Ind.– Indiana Department of Natural Resources (DNR) officers and police agencies are investigating the death of a 14-year-old boy in Sullivan County.
Police responded to the scene around noon Monday in the 4100 block of West State Road 154.
Jacob Setter, 14, of Graysville, was pronounced dead on the scene. Police say the shooting occurred in a wooded area behind his home.
No other details were immediately released. An autopsy is scheduled for Tuesday morning at Terre Haute Regional Hospital.
